<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="1292" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1292">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 855.48/7</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in Belgium</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WB1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Whitlock</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-19">
                                <hi rend="italic">October 19, 1914</hi>.</date>
                        </dateline>
                        <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                        <p>39. Your 548 [21],<note n="1" xml:id="d1292fn1">Telegram 21 of October 16
                                was transmitted through the Embassy in Germany as its No.
                                548.</note> 16th. The plan of the Belgian committee in Brussels to
                            import foodstuffs for poor of Brussels has been approved by the German
                            Government and the Embassy in London has been so advised.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>